{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol\/free()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol\/init_()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol\/readerLock()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol\/readerTrylock()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol\/readerUnlock()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol\/writerLock()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol\/writerTrylock()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol\/writerUnlock()"],"anchor":"Instance-Methods","title":"Instance Methods","generated":true}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/staticrwlockprotocol"]}],"abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" struct represents a read-write lock. A read-write"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"lock can be used for protecting data that some portions of code only"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"read from, while others also write. In such situations it is","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"desirable that several readers can read at once, whereas of course"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"only one writer may write at a time."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"StaticRWLockProtocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" : "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib14PointerWrapperP","text":"PointerWrapper","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Take a look at the following example:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":null,"code":["  GStaticRWLock rwlock = G_STATIC_RW_LOCK_INIT;","  GPtrArray *array;","","  gpointer","  my_array_get (guint index)","  {","    gpointer retval = NULL;","","    if (!array)","      return NULL;","","    g_static_rw_lock_reader_lock (&rwlock);","    if (index < array->len)","      retval = g_ptr_array_index (array, index);","    g_static_rw_lock_reader_unlock (&rwlock);","","    return retval;","  }","","  void","  my_array_set (guint index, gpointer data)","  {","    g_static_rw_lock_writer_lock (&rwlock);","","    if (!array)","      array = g_ptr_array_new ();","","    if (index >= array->len)","      g_ptr_array_set_size (array, index + 1);","    g_ptr_array_index (array, index) = data;","","    g_static_rw_lock_writer_unlock (&rwlock);","  }"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This example shows an array which can be accessed by many readers"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(the "},{"code":"my_array_get()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" function) simultaneously, whereas the writers","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"(the ","type":"text"},{"code":"my_array_set()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" function) will only be allowed once at a time"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"and only if no readers currently access the array. This is because"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"of the potentially dangerous resizing of the array. Using these","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"functions is fully multi-thread safe now."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Most of the time, writers should have precedence over readers. That"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"means, for this implementation, that as soon as a writer wants to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"lock the data, no other reader is allowed to lock the data, whereas,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"of course, the readers that already have locked the data are allowed","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to finish their operation. As soon as the last reader unlocks the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"data, the writer will lock it."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Even though "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" is not opaque, it should only be used","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"with the following functions.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All of the g_static_rw_lock_* functions can be used even if"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_thread_init()"},{"text":" has not been called. Then they do nothing, apart","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"from g_static_rw_lock_*_trylock, which does nothing but returning "},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A read-write lock has a higher overhead than a mutex. For example, both","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_static_rw_lock_reader_lock()"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_static_rw_lock_reader_unlock()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" have"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to lock and unlock a "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":", so it takes at least twice the time","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to lock and unlock a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock","isActive":true},{"text":" that it does to lock and unlock a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":". So only data structures that are accessed by multiple"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"readers, and which keep the lock for a considerable time justify a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". The above example most probably would fare better with a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol exposes the methods and properties of an underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GStaticRWLock"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"The default implementation of these can be found in the protocol extension below.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"For a concrete class that implements these methods and properties, see ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Alternatively, use "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockRef","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" as a lighweight, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unowned"},{"text":" reference if you already have an instance you just want to use.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"relationshipsSections":[{"type":"inheritsFrom","title":"Inherits From","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper"],"kind":"relationships"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockRef"],"kind":"relationships","title":"Conforming Types","type":"conformingTypes"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"StaticRWLockProtocol"}],"role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"externalID":"s:4GLib20StaticRWLockProtocolP","roleHeading":"Protocol","fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"StaticRWLockProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"StaticRWLockProtocol","symbolKind":"protocol"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/StaticRWLockProtocol/readerUnlock()":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol\/readerUnlock()","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"readerUnlock","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"()"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/staticrwlockprotocol\/readerunlock()","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Unlocks "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lock"},{"text":". If a thread waits to lock ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lock"},{"type":"text","text":" for writing and all"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"locks for reading have been unlocked, the waiting thread is woken up"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and can lock "},{"code":"lock","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" for writing.","type":"text"}],"title":"readerUnlock()","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","role":"symbol","deprecated":true},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/StaticRWLockProtocol/writerTrylock()":{"abstract":[{"text":"Tries to lock ","type":"text"},{"code":"lock","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" for writing. If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lock"},{"type":"text","text":" is already locked (for"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"either reading or writing) by another thread, it immediately returns"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"false","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". Otherwise it locks ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lock"},{"type":"text","text":" for writing and returns "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"text":". This","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"lock has to be unlocked by "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_static_rw_lock_writer_unlock()"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"role":"symbol","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/staticrwlockprotocol\/writertrylock()","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol\/writerTrylock()","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"writerTrylock","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"}],"title":"writerTrylock()","deprecated":true},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/StaticRWLockProtocol/init_()":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/staticrwlockprotocol\/init_()","title":"init_()","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol\/init_()","deprecated":true,"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" must be initialized with this function before it"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"can be used. Alternatively you can initialize it with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"G_STATIC_RW_LOCK_INIT","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"init_","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"()","kind":"text"}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/StaticRWLockProtocol/free()":{"type":"topic","title":"free()","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/staticrwlockpr